# Brand-Neutral Core

This repository is a universal context-management engine. Keep source code,
package names, comments, documentation, examples, tests, fixtures, and commit or
PR text neutral unless the user explicitly asks for a product-specific artifact.

## Rules

- Do not bake chat-specific product, brand, mascot, companion, customer, or app
  names into this repository's code or general documentation.
- Treat names mentioned in chat as external use cases, not as core terminology.
- Prefer generic terms such as `project`, `workspace`, `agent`, `companion`,
  `tool`, `source`, `artifact`, `context pack`, `adapter`, and `runtime`.
- Design public APIs so different brands, companions, and products can configure
  their own names, rules, skills, tools, and policies on top of the core.
- If a concrete example is needed, use neutral placeholder names like
  `ExampleProject`, `ExampleCompanion`, or `example.com`.
- Keep product-specific integrations outside the generic core unless they are
  expressed through adapters or configuration.

## Boundary

The core may support branded downstream systems, but it must not depend on their
identity. Brand and persona belong in configuration, adapters, or consumer
applications, not in the reusable engine.
